
🛡️ Cyber Attack Trends by Sector
📖 Overview

This project explores cyber attack trends across industries such as finance, healthcare, government, IT, and energy.
The objective is to identify:

Which sectors are most frequently targeted

Year-wise changes in cyber attack intensity

Common attack types affecting each industry

The analysis was performed in Python using Jupyter Notebook, with data visualization to highlight key insights.

📊 Dataset

Source: Publicly available cyber attack dataset:-  Kaggle

Format: CSV file with columns:

Year

Sector

Number_of_Attacks

Attack_Type 

📌 Dataset file: data/cyber_incidents.csv

⚙️ Installation

Clone the repo and install dependencies:

git clone https://github.com/shrivastavaisha23/ README.md/cyber-attack-trends by sector.git
cd cyber-attack-trends
pip install -r requirements.txt

🚀 Usage

Open the Jupyter Notebook for full analysis:

jupyter notebook notebooks/analysis.ipynb


Or view the static report directly:
👉 analysis.html

📈 Results & Insights

Key findings from the analysis:

📌 Finance and Healthcare sectors are consistently the most targeted.

📌 A major spike in attacks was observed in 2020–2021, coinciding with remote work adoption.

📌 Ransomware and Phishing dominate as common attack vectors.

Sample Visualizations:

Top Attack Vectors (bar chart)

Cyber Attacks Over Time  (line chart)

Frequency Of Cyberattacks By Sector (bar chart)

